  "description": "<i>Final Exam</i> is a multiple choice text adventure game for the 8-bit Atari.<br><br>The player has a big test coming up, and they must accrue 100 study units to successfully pass the exam.  The player encounters a number of text-based scenarios, and must choose their response, and each response will cause the player to gain or lose a certain number of energy and time units.  Events that can alter the player's energy and time include a kegger next door, disruptive flight patterns, a homicidal ex-girlfriend, your roommate's drug score, and your amorous girlfriend.  These banked time and energy units can be converted to study units.",
